          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fine-Tuning from Feedback"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fine-tuning updates model weights to encode patterns that prompting cannot reliably instil: consistent tone across thousands of turns, precise domain vocabulary, or behavioural constraints that must hold even when the user pushes back. When feedback has accumulated hundreds of high-quality corrections or preference pairs, fine-tuning is the highest-leverage lever available \u2014 but it is also the most expensive and least reversible. This topic covers how to prepare feedback data into the formats required by supervised fine-tuning (SFT) and direct preference optimisation (DPO), and how to validate a fine-tuned checkpoint before rolling it out."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Fine-tuning pipeline from feedback collection through SFT/DPO training to eval-gated deployment",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Fine-Tune"
