            "text": "Fine-tuning from feedback updates model weights with patterns that prompting cannot sustain across thousands of turns. SFT trains on (messages, ideal_output) pairs exported from human corrections with edit ratio >= 0.15. DPO trains on (messages, chosen, rejected) triples from preference pairs with confidence >= 2. Both require a held-out validation set, deduplication before training, and a regression eval across all tracked dimensions before rollout. Shadow mode lets you compare the fine-tuned checkpoint against production on live traffic at zero user risk before the full switchover."
